The food is great, the service is great. I used to come here all of the time, but in the past month, the friendly workers have stopped wearing masks. We are in a pandemic and there is an executive order that employees must wear masks when interacting with customers. This is unacceptable and a public health hazard.  "On April 12, 2020, Governor Cuomo issued Executive Order 202.16, directing essential businesses to provide employees, who are present in the workplace, with a face covering, at no-cost, that must be used when in direct contact with customers or members of the public during the course of their work."  Believe me, I wish that we didn't have to wear masks as much as the next person, but the truth is that we are still in a pandemic where many people have gotten sick, lost jobs, lost homes, and lost their lives. Please don't take this lightly.  October Edit: they have been better with wearing masks, thank you!

Middle Eastern Halal Cart located in Bay Ridge on 69th Street offers one of the tastiest foods in New York. Eating here never disappoints. Best thing about this cart is that its locally owned by brother Jojo. Brother Jojo has been there since the beginning for Bay Ridge serving the finest halal platter that neighborhood has to offer. This cart is one of the originals that started in this neighborhood and absolutely a necessary for everyone to try.  The cart has vegetarian friendly options. The falafel plate with some rice, salad, white and hot sauce is absolutely a banger. I enjoy this more than the meat. For the people who enjoy meat, this cart happens to have some of the tastiest lamb I ever tried. My recommendation would be a mixed platter with all the sauces.  Best thing about this cart is that the food always leaves you feeling good. Partially because I believe the quality is always up to standards. You can find Jojo here most of the time and next time you do, share some good vibes with the brother and share your story.  Sometimes the wait can take long and be prepared to stand in a line. This cart does get packed. Please keep in mind that is an absolute gem to all the locals of Bay Ridge and the cart is very admired in the neighborhood.
